<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-816-032  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 816 032.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>EDGE on andamp; about ATandamp;T  August 27, 1990 v5 n109 p5(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EDGE Publishing 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Threats to ATandamp;T: US Sprint claims lead with digital/fiber-optictechnology.andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   US Sprint Communications Co. (communication systems).andO;Topic:     CompetitionDigital CommunicationsFiber OpticsNetworksPublic RelationsMarket Penetration.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>THREATS TO ATandamp;T: US SPRINT CLAIMS LEAD WITH DIGITAL/FIBER-OPTIC  TECHNOLOGYandM;US Sprint issued the following statement last week:andM;US Sprint's parent company, United Telecom, recognized the superiorcapabilities of an all digital, fiber-optic network in the early 1980's.andM;We've been the leader in all aspects of implementing that far sightedstrategy.andP;  Our network was installed by early 1988.andP;  Since that time, ourcompetitors, and indeed the entire telecommunications industry, have come torecognize the advantages of an all digital fiber technology and have beenplaying catch up.andM;Even MCI's announced strategy, which still does not promise to deliver anetwork until next year, suggests a patchwork of capabilities andtechnologies.andP;  US Sprint has a long-distance network in place that no oneelse has -- the only nationwide, all digital fiber-optic network.andM;US Sprint will continue to lead its competitors because it owns and operatesa homogeneous network designed to be totally compatible and integrated withcommon digital switching and transport technology.andP;  We own the capacity andhave the flexibility to make a seamless worldwide network.andM;US Sprint's one-of-a-kind network allows us to deliver the best sound qualityand unsurpassed voice, data, and video services to all customers.andP;  Mostimportantly, US Sprint has these capabilities now.andP;  While others are playingcatch up, we'll be moving ahead with leading edge technologies.andO;</TEXT></DOC